{"accepted":[{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Formalization.","id":"vf_08ce37a83e269aee","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #165: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Give an asymptotic formula for $R(3,k)$. Current best: It is known that there exists some constant $c>0$ such that for large $k$\\[(c+o(1))\\frac{k^2}{\\log k}\\leq R(3,k) \\leq (1+o(1))\\frac{k^2}{\\log k}.\\]The lower bound is due to Kim \\cite{Ki95}, the upper bound is due to Shearer \\cite{Sh83}, improving an earlier bound of Ajtai, Koml\\'{o}s, and Szemer\\'{e}di \\cite{AKS80}. The value of $c$ in the lower bound has seen a number of improvements. Kim's original proof gave $c\\geq 1/162$. The bound $c\\geq 1/4$ was proved independently by Bohman and Keevash \\cite{BoKe21} and Pontiveros, Griffiths and Morris \\cite{PGM20}. Prize: $250. OEIS: A000791. Tags: graph theory, ramsey theory.","id":"vf_5bc4562ef9bb6380","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 165 (PR #4236) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/4236.","id":"vf_6cdda84b1f15bda3","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/165.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_08ce37a83e269aee","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:165","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_5bc4562ef9bb6380","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:165","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity deri